            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.cnn.com/2015/07/01/politics/obama-note-to-castro-reestablish-ties/index.html",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " the formal re-establishment of diplomatic relations with Cuba. The U.S. planned to relax some restrictions on the country and reopen an embassy in the island nation for the first time since 1961. The move came after the Obama State Department removed Cuba from its list of state sponsors of terrorism.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“Americans and Cubans alike are ready to move forward. I believe it’s time for Congress to do the same,” said Obama, who visited the country the following year, becoming the first sitting president to do so in almost a century. “We’ve already seen members from both parties begin that work.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When Donald Trump took office, however, he altered course to apply “maximum pressure” on Cuba. In June 2017, he reimposed travel and business restrictions on the country and the following September, cut embassy staff in half. Days before Trump left office, his state department redesignated Cuba a state sponsor of terrorism.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
